1. To install docker on ubuntu
$ sudo apt  install docker.io

2. To see the docker version
$ sudo docker --version

3. To see the docker images
$ sudo docker images

4. To pull docker image from docker hub.
$ sudo docker pull ubuntu

5. To see all the containers
$ sudo docker ps -a

6. To run a docker container from a docker image in interactive terminal mode.
$ sudo docker run -it {Images_Id}

7. To run a docker container from a docker image in detached mode.
$ sudo docker run -d {Image_Id}

8. To remove a docker container (stop it + remove it)
$ sudo docker stop {Container_Id} - stop it
$ sudo docker rm {Container_Id} - remove it

9. To remove a docker image
$ sudo docker rmi {Image_Id}

10. Pull Jenkins Image
$ sudo docker pull jenkins:2.60.3

11. To run jenkins as a docker container
$ sudo docker run -d --name myjenkins -p 8080:8080 -p 50000:50000 -v /var/jenkins_home {Image_Id}

12. To install netstat in a ubuntu
$ sudo apt install net-tools

13. To list the "LISTENING PORTS" in a server.
$  netstat -tulpn | grep LISTEN
